<br>
1) Time consuming.  A lot of people in my guild don't have the playtime to fail repeatedly while working strategies out.<br>
<br>
2) Competition.  Other guilds tend to set time limits for our guild, or they like to take over the mob if we lose.<br>
<br>
Factoring in those two, we decide to bypass the extra time and competition by reading up on strategies to make our raiding more effective.  I don't see what's wrong with that, it's just using the resources available to you.<br>
<br>
