RD here's my l33t mage advice. I loaded up my AE and went to town with the wizzies, and total resists. Scin is less than useless against these mobs, so wizzies use your magic AEs. Huge debuff at 50% totally true, what you do is at 55% have the whole raid except for like MT and 2 clerics run outside the dome, up the hill a bit and ya avoid AE. Then at...I think it was 35% the gargs pop. We get 4 druids and a backup and kite em around outside. When TT drops we bring em back in and kill them. Offtanking works too tho I guess. I am sure there are 50 diff strats and 100 ways to do this. My guild has done this mob quite a few times and we wiped just the other day when a garg killed the kiter real fast and whacked the cleric CHing the MT and he dropped, then aggro got all funny and boom we lost. Even with a strat this fight is not gimp by any means. Good luck.<br>
