<br>
I like the idea of everyone running out of the area before the AE is going to go off.    That's a good one.<br>
<br>
Like someone said, the magician AE is useless against the butterfly mobs, so either &quot;AE Group&quot; it with chanters and wizards.   If you don't have an abundance of Wizards, I think the chanter stuns could still be effective while blasting them down by normal means.   I'd put the butterfly killing crew near the clerics.    One rogue butterfly whacking at the clerics can really screw things up.   They don't have high melee output but make sure you have healers in each group.<br>
<br>
We tried TT a couple times, before we had enough people flagged, mostly for information gathering.   We knew about the adds and such, but we wanted to get a better idea on the damage output of them and stuff.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
As for the comments about spoilers, well, here's my answer:  &quot;Waaaaaaa&quot;<br>
<br>
If you're a top of the line &quot;we're the ubererist&quot; guild, then yea, no spoilers for you.   Such a shame that you'll be able to get all the pre-nerf loots.    For everyone else, I see no problem with using all the resources at your disposal.   Knowing a few tactics that others have used does not make the win, and generally you'll end up doing it completely different, as each and every guild out there has their own playing style.<br>
<br>
I like the information sharing on the forums, it's a game, and we help each other through it.   It's win-win and I see no problem.<br>
